Package civitas.celestis.util.array

Class AtomicArray<E>

java.lang.Object
civitas.celestis.util.array.AtomicArray<E>
Type Parameters:
E - The type of element to reference
All Implemented Interfaces:
SafeArray<E>, Serializable, Iterable<E>
public class AtomicArray<E> extends Object implements SafeArray<E>
An array which stores atomic references instead of the elements themselves. Since the reference objects are not externally accessible, atomic arrays can be considered thread-safe as long as the underlying elements themselves do not have thread-unsafe properties such as being modifiable concurrently.
